        To: Paul Gumsley
      From: Andrew "Mushroom" Kellett
    
û
      Text: Well Paul, I have finally managed it. After sifting through
            the thousands of SID modules that you sent me, and hours of
            typing in CED. Cheers for doing the review of Twinz by the
            way. I hope now that someone decides to actually buy it.
    
            As I have not got a working copy of WAC at writing this
            article, I can't really compare it to your magazine. Anyhow, I
            don't supose that I will get anywhere near as many registered
            users as what you have got. Still, I can dream I suppose!
    
            I managed to rip all 24 of the Koala images out of the C64
            demo that you sent me. I am currently trying to program a
            converter in AMOS, which is coming along nicely.
    
            Got to go now, but I hope to hear from you very soon ! In
            fact, I shall be talking to you in London when I give you this
            disk !!
